From ddbc49148232cae7969f0eea65b64d09d3b0e1bf Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 11:30:37 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Drive goals and summary from real user data

- Seed My Goals from the activities chosen during onboarding instead
  of hardcoded fake goals; weekly minutes now start at 0.
- Give each goal a user-assigned color + icon (picker in the add-goal
  dialog), applied consistently across goal cards, the summary donut,
  the weekly calendar, and the focus timer ring.
- Replace the streak banner and fake before/after scroll chart with a
  real weekly calendar showing minutes per activity per day.
- Rename the set-duration back label from the goal name to "My Goals".
- Add a bottom nav bar to toggle between My Goals and This week.
